# trust.list — user-side trust grants for per-project tier detection.
#
# Install location: ~/.agent/trust.list  (NOT inside any repo — the whole
# point is that this file lives outside every workspace, so plan-scope-allow
# can never auto-allow an agent editing it; changing trust always faces the
# native permission prompt. Test seam: AGENT_TRUST_FILE.)
#
# A workspace resolves to tier "personal" (earned automation — see
# docs/customization.md § Trust tiers) when its git remote origin owner
# matches an `owner` line, or its root sits under a `path` line. Everything
# else — including no trust file at all — is "collab" (cautious default).
# A repo-side .agent/trust-tier file can only downgrade to collab.
#
# Line format (stdlib parsing, no YAML):
#   owner <github-owner>     # case-insensitive remote-owner match
#   path <absolute-dir>      # workspace roots under this prefix
#
# Examples — replace with your own:
# owner your-github-username
# path /home/you/personal-projects/
